text: Karitaake Tewaaki (born December 1, 1997) is an I-Kiribati sprinter. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 100 metres race; her time of 14.70 seconds in the preliminary round did not qualify her for the first round. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:I-Kiribati female sprinters Category:Olympic athletes of Kiribati Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
